title: Setting Up a Pi-Hole via Docker
tags: docker, pihole
date: 24 Mar 2021 16:01
link: https://www.imore.com/how-run-pi-hole-your-mac

docker run -d --name pihole -e ServerIP=<SERVERADDRESS> -e TZ=America/Los_Angeles -e WEBPASSWORD=<PASSWORD> -e DNS1=1.1.1.1 -e DNS2=1.0.0.1 -p 80:80 -p 53:53/tcp -p 53:53/udp -p 443:443 -v ~/pihole/:/etc/pihole/ --dns=127.0.0.1 --dns=1.1.1.1 --cap-add=NET_ADMIN --restart=unless-stopped pihole/pihole:latest

docker exec -it pihole pihole -a -p <PASSWORD>
